dcterms:description: The FJSP is a generalization of the classical JSSP that allows processing operations on one machine out of a set of alternative machines. It is an NP-hard problem consisting of two sub-problems, i.e., the assignment and the scheduling problems.
dcterms:title: Flexible Job Shop Scheduling Problem (FJSP)

dcterms:description: The JSSP defines n jobs that consist of sets of operations of varying processing time, which need to be processed in a specific order as specified by a set of precedence constraints.
dcterms:title: Job Shop Scheduling Problem (JSSP)
